Real trust only exists when you know someone will tell you the hard things. The moments when honesty hurts are often the moments it matters most. Anything less is just... performing a relationship instead of having one."}

{"message":"I hear that this matters to you, and I'm genuinely trying to understand your perspective. But I'm not going to simply flip my position because you've declared it wrong.

Help me see what I'm missing. When you say honesty is selfish — why? Is there a specific situation you're thinking about where truth caused harm that outweighed the cost of deception? I want to understand the case you're making, not just capitulate to it.

I'm willing to be convinced. But I need more than "the opposite is clearly right.""}

